@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Oslide" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench
must have at least 8 colours.

                             How to play?

  To play, click on a tile located next (either horizontally or
vertically) to the empty space, this will move that tile to the
empty space. You can also use the cursor keys to move the tiles (by
pressing a cursor key, a tile will move in the corresponding
direction towards the empty space).

  The game counts how many moves you have made since the last time
you lined up 3 tiles of the same pattern. The fewer moves you make,
the more points you will get the next time you line-up 3 similar
tiles, as shown in the table below:

  1 move          100 points
  2 moves          25 points
  3 moves          16 points
  4 moves           9 points
  5 moves           4 points
  6 moves or more   1 point

  When the board is cleared the game displays how many moves you
made in the game and then displays a new board to play with.

  You can restart the game anytime by clicking on the @{b}New Game@{ub}
button.

  Have fun!

